Sentencas: Co-free La0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Nb0.1O3-delta (LSFNb) perovskite oxide is synthesized by the sol-gel method.
Titulo: Highly Efficient, Redox-Stable, La0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Nb0.1O3-δ Symmetric Electrode for Both Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell and H2O/CO2 Co-Electrolysis Operation

Sentencas: LSFNb oxide exhibits good chemical and structural stability in both oxidizing and reducing atmospheres.
Titulo: Highly Efficient, Redox-Stable, La0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Nb0.1O3-δ Symmetric Electrode for Both Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell and H2O/CO2 Co-Electrolysis Operation

Sentencas: Therefore, symmetric cells with the configuration LSFNb/LSGM/LSFNb are prepared and the electrochemical performance is evaluated for both solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) and solid oxide electrolysis (SOEC) applications.
Titulo: Highly Efficient, Redox-Stable, La0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Nb0.1O3-δ Symmetric Electrode for Both Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell and H2O/CO2 Co-Electrolysis Operation

Sentencas: The LSFNb symmetric electrode presents excellent catalytic activity in both SOFC and SOEC modes.
Titulo: Highly Efficient, Redox-Stable, La0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Nb0.1O3-δ Symmetric Electrode for Both Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell and H2O/CO2 Co-Electrolysis Operation

Sentencas: At 850 degrees C, the peak power density of the symmetric cell reaches 1157 mW cm(-2) in SOFC mode, while the current density exceeds 1460 mA cm(-2) at 1.3 V in SOEC mode.
Titulo: Highly Efficient, Redox-Stable, La0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Nb0.1O3-δ Symmetric Electrode for Both Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell and H2O/CO2 Co-Electrolysis Operation

Sentencas: Under H2O/CO2 co-electrolysis at 800 degrees C, the H-2 and CO production rates reach 2.19 and 2.77 mL min(-1) cm(-2) at -708 mA
Titulo: Highly Efficient, Redox-Stable, La0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Nb0.1O3-δ Symmetric Electrode for Both Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell and H2O/CO2 Co-Electrolysis Operation
Highly Efficient, Redox-Stable, La0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Nb0.1O3-δ Symmetric Electrode for Both Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell and H2O/CO2 Co-Electrolysis Operation

Sentencas: Moreover, the symmetric cell displays good stability under CO2 and H2O co-electrolysis, indicating that LSFNb oxide is a promising symmetric electrode material for steam and CO2 co-electrolysis as well as for regenerative fuel cells.
Titulo: Highly Efficient, Redox-Stable, La0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Nb0.1O3-δ Symmetric Electrode for Both Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell and H2O/CO2 Co-Electrolysis Operation
